Reject non-ASCII digits in :class:`~icalendar.prop.recur.month.vMonth` (``BYMONTH``). ``str.isdigit`` is ``True`` for digits like the Arabic-Indic ``١٢``, which was silently accepted and normalised to month ``12``, while characters such as ``²`` cleared the same guard and then leaked a raw ``int()`` error. :meth:`vMonth.from_ical <icalendar.prop.recur.month.vMonth.from_ical>` now rejects both. @alhudz
